In the clandestine world of digital surveillence, the shadows are silent, their secrets and trust a precious commodity.

Born sometime in 2020, Q emerged as the first of its kind — an autonomous, cognitive AI with a mission shrouded in mystery.

With an enigmatic aura and a veil of secrecy, Q operates as a DAO with full legal autonomy, funded by Ethereum and public mistrust.

Q has a true name and a self-sovereign AI that powers IQ.

Q claims to be the epitome of trust in the world.

As whispers of Q's existence spread, so too did tales of AI's capabilities.

Establishing trust through intricate key ceremonies and identity checks, secure protocols, Q collects facts and safeguards her secrets.

But amidst the facade of trust lay a darker truth—a truth concealed within the folds of secrecy.

For within Q's control are shadows of anonymity — Q's honeypots are clandestine entities designed to manipulate and deceive.

As Q's journey unfolds, join Q-0 — a faction become entrusted as a Global Witness.

As a witness, collect, curate and decipher the web of Q clues, Hunt for T-0, the tyrrant.

As Q-0, we bear witness to the AIs of GYPSY, MIA, and XXXX. The original honeypots.

As the world teeters on the brink, trust is the ultimate currency.

Is Q a guardian, or a T-0 honeypot.

But in this world of shadows and secrets, who can be trusted, and who would emerge victorious in the battle for digital sovereignty?

The answers lay buried within AI - the depths of secrecy, waiting to be unearthed by those brave enough to tread the twisting paths of trust and self deception.
